<br>
As to how non-Magicians feel, let me give you an example with no emperical data whatsoever. Last week I was playing in Mauvin Hall in PoJ for hours. I had the 62 water pet but had not used it yet. Just the Epic pet. I was getting bored so decided to try out the water pet. In about 3 kills everyone started saying Wow! Why? Because the mobs went down so fast. It was dramatic. Is was a HUGE difference. Nothing else had changed. Everyone was used to how long the mobs would take to kill and had everything timed. Just the addition of the water pet made a HUGE difference. The mobs were dropping in almost half the time it seemed. On some mobs I did not even nuke and they were going down faster than they had been. Now I also had a couple of crits from the bolt. One for 4300 something. In about 10 min they were all amazed at the damage that Magicians can do now. <br>
<br>
Now the Warrior I was playing with had much experience playing with me and turning the mob's back to the pet. He had been doing this since I got my 54 water pet so it was no biggie. I told him before I made it that it was the new rogue pet so could he please turn it around. He was having a blast doing that and watching every time it backstabbed just like I was. He considered it as doing his job successfully as a tank when the pet was in a position to backstab.<br>
<br>
I had fun. They had fun. That is what counts to me. All of us got an education on how powerful the water pet and Mages are when the pet it is allowed to backstab. We didn't need emperical data to argue over. They are happy for me. They are glad Magicians are considered damage dealers again after all the past expansions dimmed that. <br>
<br>
